						<summary>

						<p>Stone set up in front of the Perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Veṅkaṭa-mahārāya (I) Śaka 1523 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged and incomplete inscription gives the details of date viz., Śaka 1523 (mistake for 1524), Śubhakṛit, Mēsha, śu 13 are not sufficient for verification.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record some shares of lands from different villages purchased from several Vaishṇava individuals in favour of the lineage of the <hi rend="italic">jīyar</hi> serving the Bhāsyakārar (i.e., Rāmānuja) in the Madanagōpālanmāḍat-tiru-vīdi in Madurai. The other details are lost. </p>						

						</summary>
